[%csl Gg4] This pin is very important to solve Black's opening problems.
Although developing the light-squared bishop outside of the pawn chain is the
main idea of the Slav Defense, it remains on the same colour of those pawns,
which means that the bishop may be a source of problems in some positions. Now,
however, Black is able to exchange this bishop either for the opponent's
bishop or knight, which in either case is a favourable positional operation
for Black. In case of exchanging for the knight, Black keeps the two knights,
which can be useful in fixed structures like this. And if the exchange is for
the opponent's bishop, then White will be the side left with the "bad" bishop
on the board.} 8. Be2 {White can try other moves but none of them is good
